  "body": "<!--\r\nNeed help?\r\nRefer to our contributing guidelines for additional information about making a good issue:\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum-optimism/.github/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**\r\nOur transaction relaying utilities currently live inside of the `message-relayer` package: https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/blob/develop/packages/message-relayer/src/relay-tx.ts\r\n\r\nHowever, the `message-relayer` is a very specific service that's meant to be used ONLY for the local development environment and the transaction relaying utilities are more useful than the `message-relayer` itself. I'd rather move these utilities and their tests into `core-utils`.\r\n\r\n**Describe the solution you'd like**\r\nI think it would be best to move everything inside `relay-tx.ts` and its corresponding tests over to `core-utils`. This would make it easier to deprecate the `message-relayer`. Once this is done, we could actually go as far as making the `message-relayer` package private.",
